            <div type="textpart" subtype="dis_manibus">
               <ab><expan><abbr>D</abbr><ex>is</ex></expan><expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>anibus</ex></expan></ab>
            </div>
            <div type="textpart" subtype="body">
               <ab><lb n="1"/><persName type="cognomen" key="Faustina">Faustina</persName>
                  <lb n="2"/><choice><reg>coniugi</reg><orig>coiugi</orig></choice> suo dulcissimo
                  <lb n="3"/><persName key="Primitivus" type="cognomen"><choice><reg>Primitivo</reg><orig>Primitibo</orig></choice></persName>bene merenti<add place="right">qui <abbr>f</abbr> ano</add>
                  <lb n="4"/><add place="left"><num value="40">XL</num></add>
                      qum<note>sic</note> quo vixit annis<num value="12">XII</num> annis<expan><abbr>me</abbr><ex>n</ex>s<ex>ibus</ex>
                  <lb n="5"/></expan><num value="8">VIII</num>diebus<num value="7">VII</num>et discentes
                  <lb n="6"/>fecerunt<persName type="cognomen" key="Felix">Felix</persName> et <persName type="cognomen" key="Maximinus">Maximi
                  <lb n="7" break="no"/>nus</persName> magistro bene merenti</ab>
            </div>
         </div>
         <div type="apparatus">
             <listApp>
                <app loc="line 3">
                    <note>QUI F ANO, possible abbreviation for qui fuit annorum as attested in two similary inscriptions discovered near Rome.  See <bibl><ptr type="rest-of-bibl" target="#CIL"/><biblScope type="vol">6</biblScope><biblScope type="part">14417</biblScope></bibl>:D(is) M(anibus) / Carpophoro / bene merenti / co(n)iugi q(ui) v(ixit) a(nnos) / mecum XI m(enses) IIII / qui f(uit) an(norum) XXXXII / Muna co(n)iux b(e)n(e) m(erenti) and ICUR-01 03455: Euschemon Graecus qui fuit annor(um) / XXX et vixit cum coniuge sua ann(os) II et / mens(es) VII et dies VI reliquit filium / mens(i)um III bene merenti con/iugi Ursa fecit deposit(us) XVIII / Kal(endas) Ian(uarias) et Sisinnius frater / cum amicis suis in pace / prid(ie) Idus Decemb(res) die Martis</note>
            </app>
            <app loc="line 4">
               <note>Likely meant as cumquo instead of qumquo.</note>
            </app>
            </listApp>
         </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <p>To the Shades of the Dead. Faustina made this for her most dear and well-deserving husband Primitivus, who was in his fortieth year, with whom she lived twelve years, eight months, seven days; and also Felix and Maximinus, students, made this for their well-deserving teacher.</p>
            </div>
